My wife and I really enjoyed it all and thoroughly recommended.', 'date': 'a week ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 3, 'description': 'Fantastic place for wine - extensive list and reasonable prices. Overall I think the place is a wine place indeed but not so sure about the food quality', 'date': '2 days ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'came here for the set lunch yesterday and found that it was priced very reasonably. food was of great quality and very tasty! service was impeccable and the waitress was very attentive towards our needs. overall an extremely pleasant dining experience:)', 'date': '2 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 4, 'description': 'We visited the restaurant on a Tuesday evening. Perfect option for date night through business meetings. Curated menu offers a good array of options. Reasonably priced food and wine. Oysters are really fresh and tasty, cold cuts, pastas, steaks, beef tartare, fried rice - all solid.

PS: Restaurant Chaleur omakase upstairs is exquisite.', 'date': '3 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 4, 'description': '4.5 stars!!

Had a lovely dinner at Chef Remy‚Äôs new and aesthetically pleasing restaurant, Chapter1.
Everything we ordered (a lot!) was delicious although a couple of the starters were a slight miss for me. That said, the overall experience was very good and the service was top notch.
An absolute standout dish was as the beef tongue. It was so tender, so well seasoned, just so blardy tasty!
Can‚Äôt wait to be back - go try!!', 'date': 'a year ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': "Can't believe this place isn't busier. All the food was fantastic. We tried the Christmas Dinner menu, and the confit duck was the standout dish. Everything else was also great, but the duck was immense (and I'm not even a big duck fan). The wine choices were also good value, and the 1989 white port was a great pairing with dessert. The service was also excellent, with a relaxed but attentive team of staff. Look forward to going back soon.", 'date': '10 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 4, 'description': "4.5 Stars!!!

I found a cool new restaurant, Chapter 1, while walking around Outram area and appreciating the  architecture of quaint heritage buildings. This place caught my attention with its cool black modern signboard affixed just below an oriental style roof flanked by thick foliage. This East meets West element is done very well, enticing me to take a peek at what's beyond the entrance. And wow, a nice courtyard that is perfect for party and mingling, an idyllic porch and a classy interior.

Since I also like what's on the menu, I shelve aside my original dining plans and have a nice lunch here. And I made the right choice since the food, the wine and the service here are awesome.

Grilled Pork Secreto is so succulent with a nice layer of fat for the buttery richness. This richness is zested up by the lovely pungent aroma of the herbs in Chimichurri Butter. The accompanying Lyonnaise Potatoes is grilled to perfection where the smoky flavour enhance the taste of the potato. They are so delicious. This is one of those few times where I'm absolutely like the potatoes. The accompanying grilled onion is oh-so-sweet that I finish every strand of it. Highly recommend.

Joselito Iberico Ham, with its beautiful marbling of omega-rich fats, is lightly salted and firm in texture. When chewing on it, the complex flavours of the cured meat and fats released once again cement in my mind that this ham is one of the best hams. Parma Ham doesn't even come close. Unlike most hams with strong taste, this Iberico Ham holds subtle flavours that please the palates.

Sea Bream Crudo with Espelette Chilli, Orange Ponzu Dressing is like sashimi prepared European style, and I love it. The raw fish is very fresh and its taste is perked up by the simulating flavours of the zesty ponzu and nuanced kick of the chilli. And I like the perfectly cut orange slices lol. They tastes good when dapped with a bit of the flavourful oil the sea bream is soaked in.

Not lots of restaurants have courtyards, so I really like the courtyard of this restaurant, which gives a feeling like I'm in a mini castle or an exclusive party. Sitting at the porch and watching the world pass by across the courtyard and through the entrance is quite an experience. The interior is elegant, simple and modern with an open kitchen. And there is a long row of temperature controlled wine cabinet at the inner part of restaurant housing lots of different wines. I like sitting at the place where there are windows above me, for the different experience of sitting under windows yet still enjoying the comfort of air-conditioning and safety of the enclosure.

The service is outstanding, being very attentive, polite and thoughtful. This is a place I will think of when I want to enjoy great wine with great food.

Thoughts: Awesome Food, Wine, Service and Ambience", 'date': '8 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}]

Furthermore, at the time of the bill they asked me for a tip, even though they had already charged the 10% "service charge"; I asked him if it wasn't already included in the 10%, and was told I could leave more. It was not a good experience and I don't plan on returning.', 'date': '2 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 3, 'description': 'Booked this place to celebrate my 30th bday with my family and had one of the worst service experiences‚Ä¶

The service standard varies wildly in this place, from cordial front desk to downright rude manager(?)

As it was our first time, we asked one of the staff (believe his name was Wilson, in a black suit and bowtie) to share some recommendations.

We‚Äôd noticed one of the tables near us ordered a big pot of soup and were keen to order the same thing to share (as we were a fairly large group). It seemed like the most logical choice in terms of price, value and taste.

However, Wilson kept trying to dissuade us from getting the soup by stating it‚Äôd take 40 mins. Even though we made it clear that we were ok to have it later, and we were at the restaurant around 7.15pm.

We had to confirm that we understood the waiting time at least 4 to 5 times while ordering, which was annoying to say the least.

Was it because that soup had the most value (~$65 for at least 5pax) compared to the other soups (~$50 to $80 for 1 pax)?? Don‚Äôt put it on the menu if you‚Äôre reluctant to let ppl order it!

It was very strange to have a waiter try to stop us that many times, especially since the dish is recommended on the menu.

Also, while ordering, Wilson cut us off multiple times and did not listen to what we were saying. We had to repeat that we were flexible on the order of the food as he seemed fixated on sending them in a specific order.

The service team as a whole also seems very disorganized as we were asked about our tea choice 4 times by 4 different ppl. Even though we had alr placed our order with the first staff. There should be a better system in place.

Food-wise, the wasabi prawns (not pictured) were the best dish of the night. But not enough to save the awful service at the start.

Most of the food went downhill from there:
- Smoked jasmine tea pork ribs(?)had no smoked/jasmine tea flavor, although it was tender.
- Fried rice was bland and sad.
- Double boiled kampong chicken soup(?) was also too simple and bland, although I understand they are trying to keep the flavors pure. It just wasn‚Äôt rich or complex enough, and mainly tasted of pepper. The saving grace was the chicken from the soup, which they shredded for us; tender and tasty.
- Kailan was small and bitter

They had a unique selection of desserts, with the maotai ice cream making the strongest impression. The scoop is small, and the ice cream tastes like whisky. Worth trying once.

The coconut pudding is also innovative with its use of popping candy and boba. Don‚Äôt bother getting the pu er lychee jelly, as it doesn‚Äôt even taste like dessert (was recommended by another staff). Very bland, perhaps because it was paired with the other desserts.

To be honest, the service was so bad at the start that Madame Fan felt irredeemable. But another staff, Kent (in a white shirt), saved the experience with his polite and conscientious service.

Compared to the rest of the staff, he was very active in checking on the tea levels at different tables and prompt in clearing the dishes.

Anyway, doubt we‚Äôd be back. We were wowed by the ambience while researching this place online, and were even considering it for our wedding.

Definitely felt like we dodged a bullet with the mostly terrible service and average food.

Canton Paradise trumps Madame Fan in almost every aspect except decor. [{'rating': 4, 'description': 'Near Clarke Quay, this riverside restaurant is a nice place to stop in. Their drink selections are interesting and reasonably priced. I tried the wagyu steak for dinner, it was good. Their dessert menu is small but hefty. Enjoyed my dinner with my family here.', 'date': '3 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 4, 'description': 'So with a brighter, more open refreshed location at the far end of Riverside Point and now a refreshed menu, Brewerkz is definitely worth a visit. [{'rating': 5, 'description': "Situated on the rooftop floor of Mondrian Singapore. Visitors can access this public restaurant-bar via the lift at the 3rd floor hotel lobby.

The view is gorgeous but that was the only thing great here. Limited food options so my friend & I just got a margarita each. I got the strawberry daiquiri & she got the banana one (forgot what‚Äôs it called). The drinks tasted Pre made & mine was served with a layer of liquid on top (as seen in pic). The manager came round to ask how‚Äôs the drinks & my friend said she didn‚Äôt like hers & it didn‚Äôt taste like banana at all. The manager looked angry & just said ‚Äúthanks for the feedback‚Äù and walked away. In general all the service staff were unfriendly & rude. One even shouted at us to leave the cabana when her colleague said we could quickly take some photos there. She could have told us politely to leave instead of yelling. There was only one nice & sincere staff - Julian who genuinely wanted guests to have a better experience and bothered to change my friend‚Äôs drink for her! 2 stars because of him if not I might give 1. While making the reservation, I was also told I can‚Äôt choose between indoor & outdoor seating as they‚Äôre all subject to availability (never been told this before).', 'date': '2 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 4, 'description': 'The Mondrian a well known brand from the US with the most famous locations in LA and Miami lands in Singapore. The brand made famous by hotelier Ian Schrager and architect Philippe Stark (both famous for their own accomplishments) is known for its clean modern western architectural aesthetic infused with quirky interior design. This property a bit less quirky yet still has that DNA that has evolved over 3 decades.

Canyon club is their rooftop bar with a very impressive view of the skyline well framed by the orientation of the city. It has the prerequisites of edgeless pool, cabanas and attention to service that Mondrian is known for. If you need help they are there, is you want to be left alone with your friends they will let you enjoy the company. The drinks and food unfortunately is a let down, average and unimaginative something you get anywhere and probably better. The drink aren‚Äôt bad and good enough.

At the end of the day, come for the view! We love the girly millennial vibes here which makes it a fantastic girl night out spot especially if youre looking for a cozy new spot for initimate heart to heart talks over boozy drinks.

Also be sure to walk out inbetween drinks to take in the city view over the pool. Highly recommend!', 'date': '2 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'Fantastic service and 10/10 for the view! Except 2-3 dishes not to our liking, the rest of the dishes is fresh and perfectly done.

*Especially the crab with Uni!*
definitely a must try!

Definitely will return!', 'date': 'a year ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'Entering @oshinosg is like stepping into hallowed grounds. Their blink-and-you‚Äôll-miss-it doorway tucked in a discreet corner of Raffles Hotel Shopping Arcade belies the world beyond it - a sushi sanctuary for want of better words. The dining experience is beautiful and quite otherworldly, to say the least. My friend Vijay and I went for the Chef‚Äôs Omakase ($500++ per pax) that night and Chef-owner @k.oshino served us a goblet of Shijimi freshwater clams soup to warm our bellies before launching straight into what he is most revered for, his sushi.
A shockingly refined piece of Hirame (flounder) led the way. It had me gasping but before I could catch my breath, a Yellowjack came along and left me equally shook.
Chef Oshino then placed an elegant stand bearing Shiro Ebi (white shrimp) with Caviar, Aka Uni from Kyushu and Bafun Uni from Hokkaido in front of the each of us. I savoured that trio in quiet bliss.
Ika (squid) generally leaves me cold, but the white beauty I was presented with, dressed understatedly in salt and Japanese lime, had me longing for more.
A most astonishing Kinmedai came after, before the first streak of silver of the evening, a Kohada, arrived. I made both vanish in a flash.
Then, temperatures shifted with the arrival of a Hokkaido Hairy Crab baked with miso - I adored how the savouriness heightened the crustacean‚Äôs sweetness.
A school of ‚ÄúGlass Fish‚Äù from Hokkaido swam up next. Soft and slippery, they tasted of seaweed to me but like Vijay noticed, with a bitter finish.
The sushi continued with a stellar Sawara (Spanish mackerel) before another silver-scaled piece struck again - it was a delectably strong Iwashi (sardine) that bounced me up to cloud nine.
The following course consisted of Pen Shell, Ark Shell, Japanese Barracuda, very deliciously dressed Saury and Chutoro, and was as indulgent as it was divine.
One of my top three sushi from the meal was served at this point - the Aji (horse mackerel). I was so eager to eat it, I actually forgot to take a photo! Shocking, right? üòÇ
Anyway, sailing in after that momentary booboo was a fantastic Uni Gunkan, in all its cold, creamy magnificence.
Autumn‚Äôs gorgeous colours were captured in the triple threat of Oyster, Abalone and Ankimo (monkfish liver). Premium ingredients exactingly prepared to ensure immense satisfaction.
Moments later came the Shimofuri, a choice cut of the fatty tuna belly which melted in the mouth like I knew it would.
Topped with yuzu zest, Chef @k.oshino‚Äôs marinated tuna retained the texture of fish flesh and was not as smooth as other versions I‚Äôve tried. Not saying which is better - just appreciating their differences üòã.
The Kawahagi (Leatherjacket) boasted the best accessory - its own liver. Suffice to say, we swooned over this.
Straight from the fryer flew the Matsutake Mushroom and ginkgo nuts. They were piping hot and tasty.
For our palate cleanser, we each received a fresh Japanese Gooseberry to munch. How clever and perfect, is it not?
Then, a mini ricebowl with Ikura so fresh, my teeth felt like they were popping bubble wrap! The confetti of yuzu zest was a brilliant touch.
I was blindsided by the Scallop sushi. Wow, wow, wow - truly bowled over by the mouthfeel and taste it delivered.
The sweet and springy-fleshed Kuruma Ebi (Japanese Tiger Prawn) in the second mini ricebowl was absolutely delicious as well.
Proving yet again its ability to stop conversations was the beguilingly smoky and oily-rich Nodoguro, the last piece of sushi in Chef‚Äôs Omakase.
Our final savoury course though was a superb Tuna Cheek Shabu Shabu served with ponzu and yuzu kosho. Although it looked clean and clear, the soup had remarkable depth and flavour thanks to the fattiness of the fish. I couldn‚Äôt get enough of this!
Tamago - the edible punctuation that‚Äôs dropped in before dessert at such meals, showed up right on time. Chef‚Äôs version was bold in savouriness with a hint of sweet.
We finished with seasonal fruit from Japan. My favourite was the melon which came in a heftier wedge than the usual.', 'date': 'a year ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}]

[{'rating': 4, 'description': "Discovered this place from a friend's recommendation. One of those hidden bars in Singapore. I've walked that atreetba hundred times but never knew about this place.

The other thing that I didn‚Äôt really like was the colour. The entire place seemed to be in different shades of brown. Everything just seemed so monotonous.
It‚Äôs a very serious place. And somehow seems more for people who want to seriously discuss things or seriously study the drinks they are being served. The star of their course was definitely the Onion Jamboree. We never knew that so much taste could be coaxed out from 5 different types of onion in a single dish.
The Wagyu Cheek, usually considered a tough meat, was so well braised that the meat broke apart easily and revealed ample jelly like collagen within.
Service is attentive but not very warm. No smiling and dish introductions was spoken so fast we could hardly catch it.
Toilet provided Japanese branded mouthwash, floss and cotton buds‚Ä¶  luxurious and clean.', 'date': 'a year ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 3, 'description': 'Located along Tras Street, the entrance is a pair of wooden doors and without view into the restaurant. Atmosphere: it‚Äôs nice but I have issues with the chair, it is creaking and a bit shaky, giving me a backache after the meal.

Meal & Wine: it‚Äôs easily a 2 hour meal and the food are variations of onion ingredients. I do find some blend and personally, I don‚Äôt find the dishes wow. Plating is definitely nice. Service: it‚Äôs personable.', 'date': '5 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}]

This is an outstanding culinary experience not to be missed. First and foremost, the food is world class. Certainly one of the strongest 3 Michelin star menus I have had in recent times. All dishes were complex and multi-layered in their sensations, yet utterly delicious.

I also really enjoyed the flow of the dinner, starting at the ground floor with some excellent choice of bubbles, first nibbles and the now iconic showcase of ingredients, before moving on to the main dining room.

The wine list seemed well curated. Apart from the obvious super high end choices there was a decent range of more modest options. We had a Savagnin from Jura and a bottle of German Sp√§tburgunder, both excellent and great value.

The sommelier and the whole team were just a delight to interact with. Genuinely friendly, knowledgeable and obviously proud of what they are achieving at Zen!', 'date': '3 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'Do yourself a favour and book this place for a special occasion and unforgettable experience. Have dined here twice and each time has been unique and just as good as the first time.
Food is incredible and service is always impeccable (not stuffy which is typical of fine dining restaurants)!!!', 'date': '3 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'I had the pleasure of visiting in October 2021 and was thoroughly impressed with the exceptional quality of the food and services. Once again, congratulations on maintaining your prestigious Three MICHELIN Stars.', 'date': '3 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': "This was honestly one of the most (good) ridiculous of dining experiences here in Singapore. Given their 3 Michelin star status, it's definitely a place that you'd want to visit at least once ever, to appreciate what a 3 star f&b establishment is supposed to feel like.

We had pre-drinks next door at Mandala, before swinging over here for dinner. We ended up chatting with Chef up until past midnight, over free-flow waffles and drinks. There wasn't any air that came with Chef, as he broke down his daily life like he was any normal chef who needs to tally up his books and order ingredients for the next few weeks.

The entire team here, has a phenomenal level of passion for the craft, and aims to delight. From the moment we set foot into the restaurant, you really feel like you've entered someone's home, moving from the living room, to the dining room, then to the lounge.

Even the food served (European and Nordic flavors) were genuine. The team explains to you the ingredients from ground up, before appetizers were served. Most of the dishes were finished up in front of your eyes. It felt much more like a performance at home, just like how you'd perhaps sneak into the kitchen to watch grandma cook her best recipes.

Definitely should try once minimally, ever.", 'date': '6 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': '2nd time eating here and glad the menu has changed to the seasonal ingredients and had a wonderful suprise in each bite. The curation of flavours in each dish and the hospitality is truly worth the accolades. I love the vibe and music! The staff and service is 100% a reason on its own to come back again.', 'date': '5 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'Dinner menu. Held over 3 levels with each level with their own meals. Food were definitely amazing, indeed worthy of 3 Michelin Stars ‚≠êÔ∏è. But the amazing things were their staffs. Each & everyone were all friendly, eager to interact with diners. They almost knew what you wanted for example, when we were waiting for the lift to head down to level 1 after dinner, their staff actually brought up my car key at the exact moment without me saying. Atmosphere was very casual. Not a tinge of needing to be uptight with your etiquette.

The only slight downside was the volume of their music. It might hamper when you are trying to listen to their staffs explaining the food to you.

Other than that, definitely worth to dine at least once in your lifetime.', 'date': '3 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}]

[{'rating': 2, 'description': "Disappointing First Visit to Grand Shanghai Restaurant in Singapore

I recently had the opportunity to dine at Grand Shanghai Restaurant in Singapore, and I must say that my first visit left me feeling rather disappointed. While the restaurant had been recommended to me by a friend, my experience fell far short of my expectations.

Pros:

Ambience: The restaurant's ambience was pleasant, with traditional Chinese decor that added a touch of elegance to the dining experience.

Chinese Cuisine Variety: Grand Shanghai offers a wide range of Chinese dishes, promising an extensive selection of flavours and culinary experiences.

Cons:

Unwelcoming Reception: My visit began on the wrong foot when the front desk Chinese lady did not make any effort to guide me to my reserved table, even though it was my first time there. This lack of attention made me feel unwelcome and lost.

Inconsistent Service: As our food was served, I noticed that some guests at adjacent tables were left waiting for their orders. It was disappointing to witness the lack of consistency in serving the food promptly to all customers. We had to repeatedly call over the waitress to remind them to serve the missing portions, which disrupted our dining experience.

Lack of Attention: The waitstaff's attentiveness was notably lacking throughout the evening. For instance, they failed to refill the teapot with hot water, even when we turned the lid upside down as a signal. This neglect of basic service elements hindered our enjoyment of the meal.

In conclusion, my first visit to Grand Shanghai Restaurant in Singapore was not as enjoyable as I had hoped. The restaurant's beautiful decor and variety of Chinese dishes are overshadowed by the unwelcoming reception, inconsistent service, and a lack of attention from the waitstaff. While the potential is there, there is significant room for improvement in customer service and attentiveness to ensure a more pleasant dining experience for guests.", 'date': '4 days ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 4, 'description': 'Attended the UFM1003‚Äôs 22nd Birthday Celebration at this restaurant recently.

Truly impressed by the dishes they served!  So delicious & each portion served was just nice!

Their service staff are mostly elderly who are experienced, efficient & polite.  Very much better than some places that hire temp‚Ä¶

Their herbal soup is super nice! & the dessert is a ‚Äúkiller‚Äù!

Will definitely be back again :-)', 'date': '2 weeks ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 4, 'description': 'the atmosphere here with the live band was fantastic; the singer and musicians were great. would rate 5 stars for the band!!! delicious and unique dishes, but the restaurant service was quite slow‚Ä¶ our dishes took quite a long time to be served, with the  paofan taking the longest at about 1 hour :(', 'date': 'a month ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'Food taste great but quite pricey.  Kudos for the attentiveness of all the staff and fantastic service rendered to my family!  There is a live band and the singer sang very well for all the popular Chinese and Cantonese songs too!
An overall praiseworthy experience I had!', 'date': '2 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'Live music that reminisces the 1930s jazz era of good old Shanghai is the coolest & unique experience in Singapore. Great appeal if one loves nostalgia & digs the Chinese shidaiqu Êó∂‰ª£Êõ≤. Songs by the likes of divas Âë®ÁíáÔºåÂßöËéâ are performed tastefully here. The singer is elegant and did good interpretations for the classics.

Special mention to the manager, David, and the service staff - kind, good sense of humour & very attentive. Service staff warmly accommodate our request to sit near the stage and constantly check in with us throughout dinner.

The smoked duck is very tender & skin crispy! Scallion noodles is so springy to the bite. Egg white ball dessert w red bean & banana is refreshing though I prefer more banana in the filling.

Will come back again for more good old Shanghai vibes.', 'date': '3 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'Enjoyed every dish here -- and we tried everything from their stir fried long beans to fish (Shanghai style and steamed fish) and cold chicken etc. Service is impeccable. What an absolutely beautiful space and as icing on the cake, the band plays classic mandarin songs helmed by an amazing singer that totally gives you the 1920s Shanghai vibe', 'date': '5 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'Celebrate my in law birthday here. Service very good, food very tasty (especially roasted duck)‚Ä¶ I‚Äôm definitely will come back again.', 'date': '2 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'GRAND SHANGHAI RESTAURANT

A Tribute to the Paris of the Orient ‚Äì Grand Shanghai reopens with a brand new look and refreshed menu

Came for wedding dinner. The new Grand Shanghai rated number one by TripAdvisor among the Chinces restaurants, promises a feast for the senses. Inspired by Shanghai‚Äôs golden age of the 1930s, when it was known as ‚ÄúThe Paris of the East", relive the lavishness and vibrancy of Shanghai‚Äôs swanky era in cosmopolitan Singapore. Amid a contemporary ‚ÄúEast meets West‚Äù interior setting ‚Äì iconic art-deco motifs, elegant chandeliers and modern oriental designs ‚Äì Grand Shanghai invites you to immerse in a vibrant atmosphere of fanciful soirees, live bands and authentic Shanghainese fare.', 'date': '3 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}]

Yan is at the National Gallery. They change their menu at least every quarter. Happened to just try their autumn menu and the dishes are refreshingly great. From simple dry bean curd to mini pumpkin with seafood the new menu is excellent. See photos for a better description', 'date': '3 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 4, 'description': 'Located on level 5 of the National Gallery of Singapore is the Yan restaurant. It overlooks an open area on the rooftop.

Interior is spacious with plenty of seatings for big and small groups. They also have a private dining room but take note there is a minimum spending amount.

We ordered quite a variety of dishes here:

Soups
1) Double-boiled Collagen Soup with Fish Maw and Conpoy
2) Whole Coconut Combination - Braised Hot and Sour Broth

For the soups we were really disappointed. The collagen soup had a very fishy smell and taste which we did not appreciate. The braised hot and sour broth was very starchy and not to our liking. I would not recommend these 2 soups.

Mains
1) Steamed Free-range Salted Chicken "Hakka Style"
2) Sauteed Sliced Kurobuta Pork with Broccoli in Homemade XO sauce
3) Braised Eggplant with Minced Pork in Spicy Sauce
4) Wok-Fried Live Sri Lankan Crab with Pan-fried Cheong Fun in Chef's Special Pork Lard Sauce

For the mains I would not recommend the chicken at all. We struggled to finish it. It was meh. Would recommend Soup Restaurant chicken over this chicken any day.

The kurobuta was ok but the broccoli was cooked perfectly and we loved it with the sauce. The braised eggplant was super yummy. My family loved that as well as the cheong fun.

I would say among the mains my favourite was the crab cheong fun. Exceptionally tasty and the wok hey on it was legit. Would definitely be back for more of that!

Dessert
1) Chilled Mango Cream topped with Vanilla Ice Cream and Oats served in Coconut
2) Hot Yam Paste with Gingko Nuts and Coconut Milk
3) Chilled Peach Resin with Osmanthus and Aloe Vera Jelly
4) Deep-fried Chinese Pancake filled with Red Bean Paste

The yam paste was ok. The pancake with red bean was alright. But the highlight for us when it came to desserts were no. 1 and 3.

The chilled mango cream with vanilla ice cream and oats is a combination that I have not tried before but somehow it really works. It was amazing. Everything just came really well together and the acidity of the mango is balanced by the vanilla ice cream. I would highly recommend this for dessert!

The peach resin with osmanthus and aloe was a perfect end to the meal. Very refreshing and fragrant. This is more like what you would find in chinese restaurants but elevated due to the addition of osmanthus. Since the previous dessert was slightly heavier it was nice to end off on a lighter note.

In summary there are really good dishes here. Bill came up to 400+ for 3 people so it is on the pricier side for a meal here but definitely worth a try on a special occasion.', 'date': '2 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 4, 'description': 'Came for lunch with colleagues. the area was easy to locate. Very nice atmosphere. The food looks great. Taste is up to standard. Price is on the high side. Would surely come back but maybe only for special reasons. Services were good dishes split for you and served to each person.', 'date': '5 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 3, 'description': 'The restaurant's interior decor immediately bids visitors a warm welcome via its vibrant colours and hues. Besides, "Yan" means "Banquet".
We ordered Deep-fried Bean- curd Sheet with Shrimps and Chives, Steamed Xiao-long Bao (Bak-Kut-Teh soup fillings, ND special), Wok-fried Carrot Cake with Scallop, Beijing Roast Duck, Roast Pork Belly, Braised Brinjal with Minced Pork.
Apparently, the popular dishes, dim-sum, tea, desserts were more pricey, in comparison with comparable Cantonese restaurants along Orchard Rd, perhaps, due to factors of location and other recurrent costs. However, the Roast Duck and Fried Shrimps appeared to be better priced, surprisingly.
Staff were generally friendly; however, their service was somewhat perfunctory and superficial.', 'date': '2 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 3, 'description': 'Nice cosy environment. review_sample:
[{'rating': 5, 'description': 'Absolutely great experience. Booking with credit card is necessary. When arrived we waited at this fancy bar area where an appetiser is served. When you can see, the sense of touch smell and taste elevates and became more sensitive. Food and wine were great just have to be careful when consuming since we can‚Äôt see. Servers are all very passionate, friendly and professional. They told us they can‚Äôt see and we are impressed by how swift and accurate they serve. They were also very engaged in conversations with us. Menu changes every two months we were told. Highly recommended!', 'date': '4 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 4, 'description': 'Food: The food was nice. Service: Friendly staff which will guide you throughout the session
Atmosphere: The shop is nicely renovated. Cozy and comfortable reception area. Very interesting experience dining in the dark.', 'date': '3 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 4, 'description': 'Tldr: Very interesting experiential concept; Recommended for the novel experience. 3 course menu for $88++ (4 dishes per course, features seafood & red meat); 2 flight wine pairing for $30, 3 flight wine pairing for $40.

Nox is an experiential dining concept where you dine in total darkness while being guided and served by visually impaired waiters. I started off at the bar area (lit up) and got the ‚ÄòKwai Feh‚Äô cocktail ($22) - the gin and grapefruit pairing was pleasant and refreshing. They also served a small canape of celery root puree mousse & uni in a crispy cone (included in the set course), which was light with the sea flavor of uni.

For dinner proper, we had to remove and deposit any luminescent personal items (including phones) into a locker before we were brought to the pitch dark dining hall.

Nox serves a standard 3-course meal (appetiser / main / dessert) for $88. Each course is split into 4 separate dishes, making it effectively 12 different dishes over the 3-course dinner. Wont spoil the menu by sharing the exact dishes, but there was a good mix of seafood and red meat. The food was generally tasty and of good quality, although nothing spectacular. I also topped up $40 for the 3 flight wine pairing. After the meal, the dishes were revealed back at the bar area.

It was also interesting to experience how the visually impaired waiters used tongue clicks and whistles to navigate through the dining area with trays of food and drink without running into each other or dropping things. Overall a very interesting experience; highly recommended to try.', 'date': 'a month ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'A great great awesome experience!
Really quite a "eye opening" dining experience you should all try!

They were very welcoming and approachable right from the doorstep and until the end of the dining experience!

Try if you havent!
Cheers ^^', 'date': 'a month ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'A unique dining experience you need to try at least once! No photos of the food for obvious reasons, it was pitch dark and no electronic devices were allowed in the dining room. Enjoy cocktails at the lounge before and after dinner. Dining experience well organised, you are led to your table, and communication was very clear. You would imagine it would be messy dining without being able to see but meals are served in small bowls (4 starters, 4 mains and 4 desserts) which gives you variety and puts your taste buds to the rest. Your senses heighten as you are unable to see, and you can appreciate the flavours a lot more. The ingredients/dishes are revealed at the end of the meal. They also cater to dietary restrictions.', 'date': 'a month ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'This is the real BLIND DATE & the MOST UNIQUE DINING EXPERIENCE that I‚Äôve ever had in my life! üòå

I was pretty nervous at first since I‚Äôm not a fan of dark but we truly enjoyed 12 mystery dishes that are served & guided by NOX‚Äôs visually impaired hosts in their pitch-black dining room ‚¨õÔ∏è

Super impressed with their ability to communicate each other and clear explanation about what‚Äôs everything on the table! üëèüèª

Thanks to NOX for giving us a multi-sensory dining experience & sensational culinary adventure that we will never forget! Also thanks to our hosts, Halimi & Bernard for the lovely service, you guys really inspired us üòçü´∂üèª

If you never try it before, TRUST ME you have to try it guys! OH YES they will change the menu every 2 months üëçüèª', 'date': '4 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'This was one of a kind dining experience. We were warmly welcomed and our personal preferences were clarified at first. The dining area at the entrance had a very calming yet luxurious atmosphere. We were well informed of all what to expect. We were escorted upstairs while closing our eyes and carefully handed over to out host in a pitch dark room. The service was excellent, without any mishaps although we were in total darkness. We appreciated eating out food with all our other senses. It was an eye opener as to how the visually hard eat their meals. By the time of the main meal we had completely adjusted to tasting and enjoying our food without being able to see it. it was interesting having to guess all the things we were eating and remembering them as well so as to write the questionnaire given at the end of the dining experience. [{'rating': 1, 'description': 'Compared to what you find in Singapore, the Margarita‚Äôs restaurant at Dempsey Hills is a great place for great cocktails and good Mexican food! You can find a a variety for all tastes and desires, tasty and rich!

From the second you enter, order, get asked to make your last order by 21h30 and bringing the check without asking for it by 22h20‚Ä¶ and the horrible part when they close the toilets (for cleaning) by 22h20 and turning off the fans (outside) by exactly 22:30!!!! Shame guys, a place like this closing by 22h30 and pushing your clients out that early, shows how careless you are to entertain, make your customers enjoy and have another drink! Shame!!!!', 'date': '4 weeks ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'Interesting place, very nice food.
Only 2 of us, ordered some special dish tt not in menu. We saw some photos and ordered it with the waiter.

First photo: the pastry is v soft, fluffy and easy to eat.

Rest of food very decent.

Price: of cos it is on higher end.
All food prices $24-$30 each.
Had a place of side, jus hotdog and few prawns $24 üòÇ

Overall: nice.

Great for dates / chill out w friends.
Good services too!

Will I return? Maybe.', 'date': 'a month ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': "Margarita's seems to have been at Dempsey Hill forever.

This is a restaurant that survived covid and has continued to thrive. Obviously, there are reasons for this.

1. The food has never let me down each time I have come here either with family or friends. The food is freshly made and always tastes great. The sauces are also made freshly. All this effort is clearly reflected in the taste. Portions are large and generous as well.

2. The service is attentive. There are always enough staff around so you can get their attention when you want it.

3. There is a comforting ambience about this place. The restaurant is large, so there is a good feeling of being in a nice, large, well-decorated and well-maintained restaurant.

Made do with Nasi Ulam, Mussels, grilled eggplant and chicken on skewers.
Prepare to be tantalised by the aroma and seduced by the flavours! Every dish has its own unique plating too, making it all the more exciting to devour onto our lunch spread.

Staffs were very attentive to every details and prompt! Their ground crews put effort to check on my table to ensure all goes well throughout the dining hrs.

We were truly captivated by Hathaway‚Äôs culinary masterpiece.
Our first yet an unforgettable experience, from kitchen to its table service, truly commendable üëçüèº üåü
Definitely looking forward to try their coffee/ desserts next visit!
THANK U FOR HAVING US :)', 'date': '2 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'Went here for birthday dinner! Service was outstanding and we were gifted cake on the house‚ù§Ô∏è

Everything was beautifully plated and tasted as good as they looked! Star of the show was the fish curry and tempoyak. The sambal belacan was out of this world!!! I am a passive durian hater so considering im recommending their tempoyak is saying something hahaha.

Fish curry is, dare i say the best one i have ever tasted. Very fragrant, not too milky and the barramundi used was absolutely meaty. You can taste everything they claim in the menu description. I wish they sell their fish curry paste so everyone can enjoy it at homeü§§

Papaya salad is a winner too! So refreshing and such a perfectly balanced creation with hints of sweet and sourness in every bite. This would make a great summer snack for sure!

Baby squid dish is generous in terms of serving. This has a kick of spiciness which steadily builds in your mouth. But nothing too unbearable. If u can handle mala and ssamyang, you can handle this;)

Milkfish broth on the other hand is a very comforting dish. I really enjoyed the sourness of this soup. No fishy smell/taste affecting the taste of this broth!

Rawon was my least fav dish. Mainly bcos i‚Äôve never been a nasi rawon fan. But one thing i will praise them for is the way they cooked the beef. Definitely a must try when visiting this place!', 'date': '7 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'As the in-house restaurant of The Warehouse Hotel, Po Restaurant, named for its signature dish of Popiah as well as "Po Po (paternal grandmother)", Po Restaurant opened alongside it in January 2017.
.
Operated by The Lo & Behold Group, a hospitality group reowned for creating timeless and thought-provoking experiences for their guests, the menu at Po Restaurant was developed by Chef Willin Low, and thus, features impeccable Mod-Sin dishes.
.
Ambience at Po Restaurant exudes a quiet sophistication and timeless elegance. Low warm lights, softly glowing from the large round lamps, cast shadows upon the curved rattan wooden chairs, plush cushioned booths, and marble topped tables.
.
The place is cozy and intimate, seating up to 52 diners. Fine tableware contrasts the raw rattan panels on the walls, callbacks to their heritage yet designed for luxury.
.
Service at Po Restaurant is professional and attentive, with staff according each table personalised attention. They move purposefully and perform tasks efficiently, swiftly fulfilling requests.
.
Staff proactively offer to clear finished plates throughout the meal, and clean up quickly when diners leave. They take the effort to check on diners during the meal, offering condiments and seeking feedback.
.
In particular, several tables commended waitress Grace, who was graceful and made diners feel appreciated!
.
Food at Po Restaurant is Modern Singaporean cuisine. Chef Willin Low has designed a menu that features classic Singaporean hawker favourites, elevated with premium ingredients but retaining the familiar comforting taste of home.
.
Practically every component of each dish is painstakingly made from scratch. Portions are medium to large for individuals, and can be shared. Prices are reflective of a typical restaurant, budget about SGD $40 per person.', 'date': 'a year ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 4, 'description': 'Food: 4/5

I enjoyed the satay and fried soft shell crab a lot, and the wagyu cheek rendang was melt in your mouth kind of tender. Otah was good but a little painful at $18. The prawn noodles was ok, but just makes you happy when the prawns are massive (see pic). I ordered the ice cream popiah for myself and it came w 3 scoops of ice cream lol, I couldn‚Äôt finish.

To summarise, the food here was basically made with high quality and fresh ingredients, although the taste might or might not be amazing. I think it‚Äôs mostly quite acceptable though, at least you get what you pay for.

Service was very very good: Attentive, friendly and helpful. Ambience was lovely, spacious, and quiet enough to talk and have a enjoyable evening w your companions. [{'rating': 5, 'description': "This. Place. Is. Amazing.

[{'rating': 5, 'description': 'Celebrated my mother‚Äôs birthday and the staff went out of their way to make her feel very special which she and I greatly appreciate. Tiffin room is a high quality, traditional Indian restaurant that serves top-notch dishes at a reasonable price point. We started with the lahsuni paneer tikka which is freshly made and you can definitely taste the difference. Melt-in-your-mouth goodness with an added kick. A brilliant start to one‚Äôs meal. For the mains we had tiffin crab masala and the scallop coconut curry. Both dishes were knockouts. Delectable in every bite and not overly seasoned or spiced. The coconut curry was rich but its sweetness was balanced out perfectly by the use of shellfish stock. My only criticism would be that there were only three scallops, which at $68, is a bit meagre. Desserts, however, were the highlight of the meal. From the rasmalai to the gulab jamun to the pineapple halwa, all were equally excellent in their own right. [{'rating': 5, 'description': 'Came here with colleagues, ordered varieties of food and two bottles of wine. Can tell that their food is not commercialized - the menu was created for a reason. It has both indoor and outdoor seating, but I recommend sitting indoors as there is more space once you go through the counter.

The food is absolutely delicious! My favorite dish is the curly flower steak, which is cooked to perfection and served with a delicious sauce. The burrata cheese with sourdough is also amazing, and the olive oil and butter that come with it are perfectly flavored. The beef steak is also very good, and the sauces that come with it complement the meat perfectly.

There is no tap water, but if you order any drink, including alcohol, you will get free still or sparkling water. All of us seems to have a personal favourite. I really love the Crispy Potatoes, while my husband enjoyed the medium rare Blackmore Bolar Blade Steak. The Hummus and Burrata is also amazing, a mix of flavours that goes so well with each other.

The dessert is also delicious, the Pecan Tart is a must try! Absolute melt in the mouth.

Honestly I don't really know much about Wines and they serve mostly organic wines? But despite the name being a Wine Bar, I think the food is really worth going for.", 'date': 'a month ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 4, 'description': 'Wow, i was not expecting the food to be so good! Wine was great, but not worth it when you‚Äôre forced to scull ü§Æ', 'date': '6 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': "Quite an interesting wine bar along Bukit Pasoh. Food and drinks were of enjoyable quality, although prices can be inching on the higher side of the equation.

Thomas and Chanel were an absolute joy to be around, being very well versed with their menu. It's the first time I'm having this much organic wines, and I must admit that it's quite a unique experience.

This space will make for a great event hosting area, and also for date nights and after work gatherings.", 'date': 'a year ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': "Rebel Rebel truly stands out as a wine bar gem! Every dish on their menu is flavourful treat. My favourite is the hassleback potatoes with the taramasalata. The extensive wine selection ensures there's a perfect pour for every palate, and Gerald's wine recommendations are always on point.

The music playlist is also wonderfully curated, not just playing whatever that's on the trending on the charts. The vibe and ambience at Rebel is also one of a kind, chill, cosy and unpretentious.

Highly recommend for a memorable dining experience. Definitely will be coming back again and again!", 'date': '5 days ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': "This charming space is more than a wine bar; it's a journey into the realm of natural wines, showcasing a diverse selection from various regions‚Äîincluding wines from less known regions like Japan or the Czech Republic.

The ambiance is laid-back yet exudes an understated elegance, making it a perfect spot to anyone, whether you're a seasoned wine connoisseur or a curious wine drinker (like myself). It stands out for democratising wine, making it accessible and enjoyable for everyone, while many other bars maintain a fancy schmancy approach.

The knowledgeable and friendly staff readily guides you through each bottle's unique narrative and the distinct flavors borne from varied terroirs. Special thanks to Gerald for introducing me to natural wines - I have been here many times since.

The food here is also amazing - having tasted almost every dish here, you can tell every dish is a thoughtful creation by the kitchen team. To get the best experience, do ask the staff which wine pairs well with which dish - their suggestions are always on point.

A visit to Rebel Rebel always means good wine and good food - a hella good time guaranteed.", 'date': 'a week ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}]

Although everything was executed and cooked well, it was a very standard and uninspiring menu.

The service was fantastic , extremely knowledgeable and fast but this doesn‚Äôt make up for the value for money. When you go to a one starred Michelin restaurant and pay this amount, you naturally expect to have your mind blown with innovation and creativity. The taste was extremely familiar and standard, I do not recommend this place. There are other one starred and two starred Michelin restaurants serving better quality food for a lower price point. My suggestion would be to change the menu and offer different options, it seems like they‚Äôve stuck with the same menu for quite a long time, nothing exciting or new.', 'date': '3 weeks ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'On a charming autumn Sunday evening at around 6 pm, I strolled into the enchanting realm of "Art of Daniele Sperindio." Little did I know that I was about to embark on what would turn out to be my most delightful dining experience in Singapore.

As a devoted food enthusiast and someone who enjoys Michelin starred restaurants, I must assert that this culinary gem deserves more accolades than the prestigious star it has already earned.

Perched on the 6th floor of the National Gallery Singapore, the restaurant offers a panoramic view of the city skyline and Marina Bay through its floor-to-ceiling windows. Before entering, I took a moment to relax on the expansive terrace, basking in the glory of a breathtaking sunset.

Being the first guest of the evening, I was greeted with warmth and attention from the entire team. Mr. Pellegrino, the Restaurant Manager, graciously welcomed me and led me to a cozy table by the window.

The interior exuded elegance and sophistication, showcasing natural materials and contemporary design. The neutral palette of white, beige, and gray, coupled with wooden and leather furnishings, created a refined ambiance. Tables adorned with crisp white linen, exquisite chinaware, and Riedle crystal glasses added to the overall allure.

Opting for a bubbly start, I perused a delightful selection of champagnes presented by the sommelier. My choice, the Egly-Ouriet - Les Pr√©mices Brut, proved to be a light-bodied and refreshing champagne with hints of white fruit, citrus, and minerals.

The aperitif was a culinary journey in itself. From the "Chutoro tonnato with Japanese strawberry," a tender delight paired with fresh strawberries, to the creative reinterpretation of "Prosciutto e Melone" with swordfish ham and melon, and finally, a tiny puff with stracchino fondue and spring truffle sprinkles ‚Äî each bite was a revelation of flavors.

The official dinner commenced with the intriguing "Cappone Magro," a dish traditionally enjoyed during Lent, skillfully reimagined by Chef Sperindio. The presentation was a work of art, featuring Alpine milk whipped into a cream infused with Alaskan and Sri Lankan king crab, chamomile, pear, and crowned with Majestic Black Caviar.

The pasta course, Taglierini with Santa Margherita prawns and Sancho pepper, paired seamlessly with Zyme's "From Black To White, Il Bianco 2019," a rich and complex white wine suggested by Federico, the General Manager.

Continuing the culinary voyage, "Estate ad Albenga" brought the taste of Liguria with a Mozambique Langoustine, Sardinian seabass, avocado, and celery pearls, topped with a chic emulsion of Franciacorta wine and beluga caviar.

The meat course, accompanied by Quintarelli Giuseppe's Valpolicella Classico Superiore 2016, showcased the chef's expertise with low-temperature cooked New Zealand Maimoa lamb, toasted chicken skin, and a warm Marsala reduction.

Desserts were a symphony of flavors, with a pre-dessert of glazed Nashi pear and bergamot Pernod jelly, paired with Marsala Superiore "Old John" Riserva DOC 1998. The grand finale, "Tourists on Mount Vesuvio," featured white chocolate, buffalo milk gelato, and a 40-year aged balsamic vinegar infusion.

The Piccola Pasticceria, a delightful array of pastries, concluded the feast, accompanied by Recioto della Valpolicella.

In essence, dining at Art is a poetic experience. The restaurant, paying homage to Pellegrino Artusi's "The Science of Cooking and Art of Eating," seamlessly blends modern sensibilities with classic inspirations. The elegant interior, meticulous tableware, and the highly skilled team contribute to a luxurious dining affair.

Chef Sperindio's culinary storytelling, from creative amuse-bouches to hearty main courses, immerses diners in his world. Art offers an innovative, authentic, and elegant dining experience that leaves patrons both satisfied and inspired.

If you seek a culinary adventure that transcends the ordinary, Art is undoubtedly the place for you.', 'date': '2 days ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'A wonderful birthday lunch - thanks to the pleasant, attentive and warm service. A good service always a elevates the experience for us. We had the three course set and right from the aperitivo to the mains and dessert - the presentation and the dishes were spot on. You can really enjoy the individual flavours in each dish and the thought behind creating that harmony of flavours in every dish really comes through. The coriander and charcoal pur√©e in the fish dish for example just packed in the essence of coriander so well and balanced that dish. Along with the presentation, the storytelling, and the dessert highlight - it‚Äôs like one enjoyable celebration that delights yours senses. You can see the effort and passion behind every dish. We enjoyed our experience and will be back for more.', 'date': '4 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'Exceed expectation, reasonable price for the food quality and service.

The atmosphere is very good, all the table are quite far apart give guest a good space and privacy, nice view of the Padang and Mbs.

Most of the food are quite nice, the bread is impressive with the lemon infused olive oil quite interesting. The caviar dish is nice with the generous portion of caviar given.

Celebrated the bday here and they even provide extra dessert for the birthday on top of the dessert from the menu.

We are unable to finish The food and they even pack the last dish in a very nice paper box that looks like for jewelry or gift, very very nicely done. Will be back for next occasion!', 'date': '5 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': "We had an absolutely wonderful experience at ART di Daniele Sperindio. The exceptional service provided by the Restaurant Manager Pellegrino made our visit truly memorable‚ò∫Ô∏è Moreover, the restaurant's view of celebration of the Singapore National Day rehearsal added an extra layer of enjoyment to our evening. The nice botte of wine, the lively atmosphere, and the delicious Italian cuisine all came together to create a perfect evening. I can't thank Pellegrino and the entire team enough for their outstanding efforts. We‚Äôll definitely be returning soon to relive this fantastic experience!", 'date': 'a month ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}]

While some of the service staff are new and genuinely try their best, it's the manager who seems to lack leadership and poses a problem. To make matters worse, when his staff came to the table to surprise my friend with a birthday cake, the manager approached us at the exact same moment to ask for payment. I found myself torn between paying the manager on my left or singing the birthday song and celebrating my friend's special moment on my right. Eventually, I paid first and requested that they prioritize and handle one task at a time in the future.

I have been a patron of PS CAFE since 2013, dating back a decade at Harding Road outlet. ‚≠êÔ∏è The wines are very good and very good price.', 'date': '8 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'My first visit to the one & only Sicilian restaurant in Singapore. Since Sicily is an autonomous island near Italy, the cuisine has noticeable Italian and Mediterranean influences, okay, this looks really promising. After a Sicilian Journey here, I can say I'm now a fan of Sicilian cuisine.

A taste of Sea Scallop Ceviche, Smoked Caviar makes one feels like he or she is dining in a beautiful seaside town. This is such a beautiful dish, in terms of both aesthetic and taste. The fresh, plump, juicy scallops is so full of briny sweetness, accentuated by the intense umami of smoked caviar, zest of the tomato and clear sauce. I love this so much.

Bunny Kombucha of Passion Fruit flavour is very refreshing, slightly sweet and sour. Great for the health of the guts and really whets the appetite. Very good recommendation by the friendly and helpful service staff.

Amuse Bouche of Truffle with Ricotta Cheese has the super creaminess and mild nutty flavour of ricotta cheese paired with the earthy aroma of truffle. The thin wafer adds a nice crunch to the dish. A well-executed starter that explores the combination of various tastes and textures.

Sourdough bread is served warm and has a nice fluffy texture Very wholesome treat, and the olive is very interesting in taste, having a slight astringent bitter taste with planty notes. I like this unique taste.

Sicilian Rice Balls, Fresh Black Truffle, Ragusano Cheese Fondue comes after Scallop Ceviche, and this is like trip from the seaside to the deep woods. More mellow, features the nuanced flavours of the earth and woods, this dish is a nice transition in taste profile. The fluffy, starchy rice packed with molten cheese, peppered with truffle, is so wholesome in taste.

Risone Pasta, Baby Octopus, Bone Marrow Butter is another great surprise served. The baby octopus is springy in texture and yet easy to bite, I definitely prefer this over the regular tough octopus. I love the Risone Pasta. It has the wholesomeness of quality rice, and its grain-like shape allows the rich sauce to fully coat each grain, so each bite of this is bursting with flavours. The texture of this paste is unique and unbelievably good, having smooth exterior with starchy interior. First time ti try to kind of pasta, and I'm lovin' it already.

The service staff is very nice to change my mains to Citrus Glazed Iberico Pork Belly, Parsnip, Wild Spinach from the lunch menu since I prefer pork and seafood over beef, lamb and fish. This has nice tender pork with rich gamey flavours, and mustard and special sauce to cut through the gamey flavours for the balance in taste. Very favourful and hearty.

Tiramisu, Noto Almonds, Amaretti Crumble is a indulgent treat with lots of creaminess, hints of alcohol and nutty goodness of almonds. This nicely round up the whole exciting trip of a meal.

The place is so beautiful. The exterior looks like a well-furnished bungalow with a courtyard. The first floor is seeped in idyllic theme, like the backyard patio of a mansion, perfect to chill out. The second floor is posh and fancy, like the main dining hall of the very same mansion. Lots of instagram-worthy pictures can be taken of the place. The service is excellent, being friendly, enthusiastic and attentive, and they have very good knowledge of the food. Now I can add another favourite type of cuisine into my Favourites List, and it is Sicilian. Since it is in my Favourites List, of course, I will come back for more.

Thoughts: I love all dishes here. [{'rating': 5, 'description': 'Amazing.

Location:
Beautifully crafted and recently renovated. It gives you the feeling of being included in the process of their art, yet it still also feels intimate. I was lucky to have one of the seats at the counter to directly watch the talented cooks work their magic. Amazing Artwork shown here as well. It really balances traditional elements with rebel culture art. I adored the music they chose - it was a mixture of pop classics and some indie songs and consists of the favourite songs of the chef. For me personally it made the whole experience feel extremely personal as it was a pretty good match to my own spotify favorites. Loved it, we need more of this instead of the run-of-the-mill classical stuff.

Food: Officially eight courses but a variety of snacks was also offered. The menu had a very good progression overall and was bursting with flavour. I especially loved the quirky combos - licorice bread, artichoke or laksa leaf ice cream. The coconut broth that came with the lobster course was just a warm, heartfelt culinary hug.

Drinks: Although i started with some bubbly I opted for the nonalcoholic pairing - this was also one of the main reasons for having chosen Cloudstreet. The pairing made sense to me with highlights being the pairing for the Wagyu and the smoke on the water.

Service: As you would expect from a two star restaurant. Everyone was very professional and eager to make my experience as smooth as possible. There was one hiccup when they sent me the alcoholic beverage pairing instead of the nonalcoholic pairing for the dessert. For me it is not a big issue, however I guess someone who cannot drink alcohol for health or religious reasons might take more offense to that. But mistakes happen and I probably should have also noticed that the drink is not non-alcoholic when it was presented. Everything else was absolutely impeccable.

Attitude: I went to Cloudstreet by myself and the team took such great care of me. I was a little apprehensive to go to a fine dining restaurant by myself, but they made me feel very welcome and included. I enjoyed a lot of the conversations and it felt very personal.

Thank you so much for this amazing experience. [{'rating': 5, 'description': 'Had the Epicure course. A good variety. Delicious. Service excellent. Room cosy.
But the chilled mango cream pudding taste was overwhelming. Too concentrated and too acid. Smell never leaves after eating no matter how much tea to wash off. From the moment you step inside, you'll adore the cozy ambiance and welcoming decor. The attentive servers transform a simple meal into a memorable experience, and the talented chefs deliver an explosion of flavor that will leave your taste buds wanting more.

The food menu is extensive, featuring both classic and modern dishes, all handmade with the freshest ingredients. Every bite is a treat, with savory and sweet varieties filling your palate with delight. Don't miss out on the steamed shrimp in pepper, Wagyu beef, and the beautiful egg tarts. Besides that, the restaurant also offers a wide range of Cantonese dishes, from roasted meats to seafood specialties.

The steaming hot dishes from the wok are a particular highlight, with the chefs masterfully balancing each ingredient for the perfect texture and taste. Seafood lovers will relish the fresh lobster, crab, scallops, and fish cooked to perfection with delicate Cantonese flavors. And of course, no Cantonese meal would be complete without a bowl of rice, and the restaurant offers steaming bowls of fried rice, congee, and other rice dishes.

In summary, Shang Palace is a must-visit for those craving authentic cuisine with mouth-watering dishes and an atmosphere that engages all of the senses. A fantastic place to enjoy a meal with loved ones or celebrate a special occasion. review_sample:
[{'rating': 5, 'description': 'Super cozy & aesthetic thai bar.

They also serve interesting cocktails with various Thai liquor! Bonus points as they have Guiness on tap too. Their selection food items are limited but it‚Äôs one of the tastier bar foods that I‚Äôve had. Special mentions to the Prawn Vermicilli (very flavourful and generous large prawns were given) and moo ping (served in skewers or with buns, charred perfectly with some crispy edges but juicy and succulent with every bite).

Although food service is a bit slow at times, drinks are always served promptly and the staff are always so friendly!', 'date': '2 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'Excellent venue to relive a mini-Thailand in Singapore. Excellent & authentic tasting food, Thai inspired cocktails & great value for money beers.

Simply can‚Äôt go wrong in this cozy place, dim and simultaneously neon bright lights.

Will be back for sure.', 'date': '4 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': "Come for the famed prawn vermicelli, but stay for the amazing cocktails and great music.

My favourite-est part about Fin has to be the music: I don't think there are other Thai bars with a similar playlist like Fin (think: Top40s T-pop and T-rock, with the likes of Three Man Down, Tilly Birds, Bowkylion, Jeff Satur and Paper Planes)

Drinks are also affordable (compared to bars in the area), and Fin's bossman makes a wicked cocktail - you must try the Whiskey Sour or the Golden Mile cocktails!

The prawn vermicelli (Goong ob Woonsen) is definitely the star on the menu, but one underrated menu item to try is the spicy lime fish fillet: the steamed fillet is always fresh and the gravy is super addictive. The lightness of flavour is also a great contrast to the rich umami of the prawn vermicelli.

If you are the in area on weekday evenings, do try their dinner set menu - it's reasonably priced and lets you sample the best of everything (including the vermicelli!).

Fin is a great place to hang - whether you're doing a post-work meal, or a gathering of friends over drinks, you're going to have a good time with good music and good food.

Like what other reviewers have noted, the place can be a bit tricky to find in the mall.

If you are arriving by taxi, alight from the drop off point, walk past the security post, make a left and take the escalator down. If you are arriving from other exits in the mall, look for the Juewei ÁªùÂë≥ shop, and take the escalator down. Fin is right beside the escalator!", 'date': '7 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': "For enthusiasts of melodious tunes from Thailand, this spot should be on your bucket list! It's nestled secretly in the subterranean level of the shopping complex, a treasure waiting to be discovered. For ease of access, utilize the ingress point next to the cab queue.
The gastronomic delights here are nothing short of amazing! With a creative spin on the traditional Thai fare, it certainly pleases and surprises the tastebuds.
But the experience doesn't stop with the delectable dishes. The establishment marries contemporary mixology trends with their dining concept in a way that's captivating and memorable.

[{'rating': 5, 'description': 'It‚Äôs simply awesome. The team and owner was so warm and amazing. Had the best New Year eve evening at Revival. The cocktail and bartenders were so creative on their drinks last night. We really enjoyed ourselves and wished to thanks this 5-stars establishment for a wonderful evening on such a chic decor premise. Happy New Year once more guys, your warmth and kindness will make me come back soon! ü•Ç', 'date': '9 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'This was a real find! I had heard that this River Valley cocktail bar opened quite recently, and visited twice to sample different cocktails and dishes from their kitchen. Both times I had a five star experience.

The cocktails are very innovative and each one is inspired by a famous artwork. This is a really cool concept! The Marcelle Lender "Dancing the Bolero" was my favourite so far - a rye whiskey-based concoction that's perfectly balanced, like a better, more complex version of an Old Fashioned. The Portrait of Pablo Picasso was likewise excellent, and I can't wait to try The Scream (it was unavailable for both of my visits, sadly).

The big surprise here, other than the top-flight quality of the cocktails, is how good the bar food is. The small-plate dishes are superb - the creamed spinach and artichoke dip with roasted sourdough bread is die-die-must-try and the veggie quesadillas are very tasty too.

The bar is a little hard to find, set back from RQ with no sign over the door as far as I could see, but it's 100% worth seeking out. The vibe is classy but friendly, the drinks and food are great - hats off to whoever designed the cocktails and the food menu, because you did a great job! This is already my favourite cocktail bar in Singapore. Don't miss it!', 'date': 'a year ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 4, 'description': "Located on the quiet end of Robertson Quay, Revival is a cocktail bar founded by bar veterans The Compound Collective. With plenty of plush seating, the mood is laidback and unpretentious. Named after art pieces, its tipples are exciting and fun to drink.

[What it's good for]
The Liver is the Cock‚Äôs Comb (S$22) smelled of summer with red berries and lily, while the oat milk distillate rounded off the Plantation 3 Stars white rum in it. The Lady of Shalott (S$22) was a tangy version of a pisco sour made sweeter with Lustau Fino sherry and sweetcorn.

The more robust cocktails included Esfinge ‚ÄúThe Sphinx‚Äù and The Scream (S$22 each). The Sphinx was a deliciously savoury and complex mix of carrot ferment, ginger, honey, acid and Ichiiko Saiten shochu that was gently fizzed with CO2. The spiciest of them all was The Scream, a fiery take on the margarita and bloody Mary combined, made with Ardbeg whisky, Codigo 1530 Blanco tequila, smoky Ancho Reyes chilli liqueur, chipotle distillate, red capsicum, lime, and agave.

[What it could improve on]
The food options were lacklustre. The smoked salmon roll (S$18) came as four measly slices of toasted bread with rolls of the smoked fish on top.

[Our quick takes]
Is it conducive to conversation? ‚Äî When it‚Äôs less crowded, the Main Room has plenty of corners to sink into for a good conversation. But given its limited indoor space, an al fresco sofa would be your best bet.
Is a reservation necessary? ‚Äî Yes. Although it was quiet when we went, we‚Äôve no doubt that once word gets out, this hideaway will be frequented by cocktail fiends.
Takeaway recommendations? ‚Äî Revival does not have bottled cocktails at the moment.
How to get there? ‚Äî There are many bus services that can take you there from the Orchard shopping district. Otherwise, walking from the Fort Canning MRT station will take you only five minutes.

[Things to note]
There isn‚Äôt exactly a signboard at the bar, but look out for its R logo on the floor or the big bar counter that‚Äôs hard to miss.
Smoking is allowed only in the al fresco area.
The Sanctuary on the second floor is open only for private parties and events.
Revival extends a 10% discount to people working in the bar industry.

Read more at HungryGoWhere for the full review", 'date': '7 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'What a stunning bar with incredible cocktails.

When my companions and I entered the restaurant, it was very empty. The staff guided us to this room with three tables and we occupied one of them. After that, this group of around 12-14 people came in and started chattering very loudly. We requested to change tables since the noise was deafening but the staff did not allow us to. Their reasoning was that the other tables were reserved. I do not understand their reasoning because: 1. Another instance that left us totally stumped was when we ordered our food earlier than the other table in the room. However, the other table got their food first and although we waited for while longer, we still didn't get any food served to us. As such, one of my companions went to ask the staff why our food was taking so long and their response was quite hilarious. As the other table had ordered appetisers and we did not, we would be served later even though we had ordered our food earlier. I will refrain from saying any expletives but my companions and I were basically hungry and tired from their nonsense.

In total, we waited for 35mins for our food. That's too long of a waiting time when there weren't even that many tables occupied!
