review_sample:
[{'rating': 5, 'description': "Truly a 5 star experience, in this quaint rotating tower (note, you won't be affected by this as the seats face inwards, and the rotation is ever so slow)

We had the fuji set (200++) and almost every course was well prepared and tickled our taste buds (except for the first appetiser with edamame.. Bleh). This was on par and even surpasses shinji for us given the personal and friendly experience with the Exec chef and his wife.

The maguro, otoro, roll, mackerel were specific highlights - we also loved the aburi experience (not with a torch, but with a piece of charcoal for the finishing touch!). A slight comment - we felt some pieces were prepared too early in adv, and one or two pieces felt a little soft and were coming apart when we picked it up if you understand what we mean (like sashimi / sushi that's been prepared for a while and left there). But admittedly that is us being picky and trying to pick a bone, nothing to take away the 5 stars rating.

I'll strongly recommend this over the typical Michelin starred establishments.", 'date': 'a year ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'Really solid omakase from Sushi Mieda offering a wide variety of dishes that is sure to please any palate. I was blown away by the quality of everything served, especially the baby tuna and nigiri sushi. Fantastic meal all around. Hope to have another chance to visit again soon.', 'date': '2 years ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': "First time here at Mieda, had the $120 lunch set (7pcs sushi). Relatively pricey compared to other fine dining sushiyas, but definitely one of my favorite sushi experiences.

Shari here is relatively heavy on the soy sauce and red vinegar, so if you're not a big fan of that, this might not be the place for you.

Starts with a wonderful appetiser of seaweed and orange shellfish. Super umami and whets your appetite.

The 7pcs of sushi we had were (i forgot the exact order): Hirame, Isaki, Akami, Chutoro, Aji, Kuruma Ebi, Anago

All the sushi were yummy, my favorite being the Aji. The chef has a tendency to add citrusy, acidic components to his sushi which I think is what sets Mieda apart from other sushiyas. First time having akami/chutoro in such ways.

Uni ikura don is a small portion and comes with small diced white fish. You can't go wrong with uni ikura don, but I've definitely had better elsewhere.

Dessert was matcha ice cream, azuki and cherry. Couldn't really taste the matcha.

Overall, meal was well-paced, a must try if you're into sushi.", 'date': '2 years ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'This is now one of my top two sushi restaurants in Singapore.

If I was already very impressed on my first visit to @sushimieda, my second sealed it. Based on personal preference, I feel I get the highest satisfaction-to-dollar value from their Omakase. Since I‚Äôd tried the $180++ option for lunch previously, I decided to indulge in the $250++ last Saturday. To say I was extremely pleased with my decision is an understatement, because everything Chef @sushi_ohno served was ultra delicious:
1. Bonito -  Spectacular opener as the tuna creation with ponzu sauce, radish sprouts, ginger flower and shiso flower was bouquet-like in its burst of fragrance and flavour.
2. Tai - The bouncy-fleshed red snapper was accompanied by seaweed salt and fresh wasabi. Chef encouraged us to eat the fish with and without the salt - both ways were really lovely.
3. Iwashi Maki - Sardines, pickles and more, but no rice, were pressed together into the most gorgeous and mouthwatering roll.
4. Kinmedai - Shockingly good! The straw-smoked fish was presented with wakame and a paste made from shiso leaf, spring onion and ginger. Definitely one of the standouts for me from the lunch.
5. Hotaru Ika - Another favourite of mine. If you‚Äôve been scrolling through Instagram in the past month, you‚Äôd have  probably seen the firefly squid popping up on some foodies‚Äô Stories. Chef Ohno put a satay spin on it by threading a trio on a skewer.
6. Baby Ayu - A pair of the freshwater fish swam up next. To be eaten whole, these were a divine textural experience of crunch and creaminess.
7. Baby Snapper - Chef Ohno said that because the flesh of this fish is a bit sweet, he adds his own savoury shrimp powder to balance it out. Genius.
8. Sakura Masu - I am not exaggerating when I say the piece of very soft cherry trout melted in the mouth most pleasurably.
9. Zuke - The marinated lean tuna may have been on the salty side but the shari (vinegar-seasoned sushi rice) was strong enough to hold its own.
10. Chutoro - I‚Äôve always believed one of the most beautiful sights at a sushi-ya, and also one of the most insanely delicious things to come from the ocean must be the medium-fatty tuna. This was a prime example.
11. Otoro - Even fattier than the chutoro, it had a meatiness that made me think of an insanely tender steak.
12. Akagai - I gawked at Chef Ohno as he ‚Äúwashed‚Äù each large clam in a bowl of vinegar and ice before forming sushi with it. The reason for this, he explained, is to neutralise its innate sweetness. Clearly, it worked as the result was terrific.
13. Kohada - Firm and crunchy, the silvery gizzard shad with its bolder taste, was offset beautifully by the strong shari.
14. Mini Chirashi Don - Each bowl was filled with a generous amount of uni, ikura, small pieces of flounder, prawn powder, mushrooms and kampyo. Best way to enjoy it was to push the spoon all the way down, so a little of everything was captured as the spoonful made its way up to the mouth.
15. Kuruma Ebi - Usually cut into half for ladies, I requested Chef Ohno to serve my Japanese Tiger prawn whole. All the better to relish.
16. Anago - Having been smoked between bamboo leaves, the warm conger eel was as bewitching in scent as it was in taste and texture.
17. Ankimo and Kampyo Maki - Bringing up the rear, two small rice rolls. One contained monkfish liver that‚Äôd been steamed in sake, the other, strips of dried calabash gourd. Quite sensibly, I chased the rich with the crunchy when gobbling them.
18. Tamago - Heard there‚Äôs prawn used in @Sushimieda‚Äôs version.  No wonder it‚Äôs complex and more umami than sweet.
19. Dessert - Japanese strawberries, sliced apple, azuki red bean and salted caramel ice-cream brought lunch to a satisfying close.

[{'rating': 5, 'description': 'The food was great given that it‚Äôs done by a Michelin star chef and the ambiance was perfect for a special celebration. One example is when my GF was coughing, one of them was serving another table and he quickly signalled to his colleague to attend to us and check on her. Versus other restos where staff tries to avoid you, here you just make a simple eye contact and they readily acknowledge. They are very knowledgeable of course on the food and makes great recos and nice simple chats to keep you interested and entertained. review_sample:
[{'rating': 5, 'description': 'Would give 6 stars on atmosphere if I could. Really cool bar and pretty great food too. The decor is really cool, especially the 4 story liquor cabinet. The bartenders are well rehearsed in their craft and look cool while they make the delicious drinks. The octopus I got was fantastic and bass was good too. Really enjoyed my cocktails. All around great experience...would love to go back!', 'date': '2 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 4, 'description': "Beautiful and best deco ever seen. This place is huge and feels like you're in a art museum.
The high tea doesn't comes cheap. Welcome champagne and desert before the cage is served. Lots of pastries to indulge in. No deep fried stuff, seafood or meat except 1 slice of smoke salmon. Too much of pastries. Probably will come again for other food.
Environment no doubt is best in the world that comes with a price tag.", 'date': '2 weeks ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 4, 'description': "The sheer opulence of the expansive space is nothing short of taking your breath away. Soaring 45-foot-high ceilings gaining inspirations from the Art Deco skyscrapers of NYC, the atlas empire is decked out in detailed ceilings and painted murals.

Smitten with the palatial beauty and decadence of the bar, it also offers the widest selection of gins to keep you intrigued. There remains a steely hype surrounding this venue and deservedly so‚Äî being on the world's 50 best bars list.

Lunch is a impeccable experience with good selection to keep one spoilt for choice. The lobster rolls, burrata salad, smoked pork loin, buttermilk chicken sandwich were scrumptious. Desserts like the pineapple granita, hazelnut tart, warm madeleines and pavlova were delectable. Service, polished and professional.

All in all, a great place to host friends, overseas guests and be sure to dress to impress.", 'date': 'a week ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'This place is absolutely stunning. The 4-storey high wine and liquor cabinet, adorned opulently in Greek style columns and gold trimmings, is a sight to behold. Intricately and grandiosely decorated throughout, the bar speaks art d√©cor inspired by 1920s Europe.

Despite being lavishly fitted out, Atlas is not an unwelcoming place. Dress codes are present, but the service is unpretentious and welcoming, the lighting dim and mood solemn but relaxed, and suitable for all occasions.

Atlas is known for its cocktails and gin, and they certainly didn‚Äôt disappoint. Being an alcohol-focused place, the food isn‚Äôt the main attraction, nothing too over the top but tasted decent and reasonably well executed.

Atlas is a bar like no other ‚Äì a place that transports you out not to another country, but another universe, like in Gotham City where Batman is looking out for you somewhere.', 'date': '3 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'My wife and I had one of a most memorable afternoon here, just loving life and love! The cocktails are divine. The atmosphere and decor is second to none and the lobster roll is top-notch. Highly recommend if you want to celebrate something special or just want to spoil yourself.', 'date': '4 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'Arguably the most stunning interior design I‚Äôve encountered in any bar.

If you‚Äôre looking to impress work colleagues or foreign friends, this is the place to book an afternoon tea or evening drinks at.

The soaring ceilings immediately command attention, exuding an ambiance of grandeur and elegance. The Atlas taster set, priced at a mere $38, offers great value. Their espresso martini stands out as the best I‚Äôve ever tasted, perfectly balanced and exquisitely crafted.

Complementing the outstanding drinks is the impeccable service, with attentive bar servers ensuring a flawless experience.', 'date': 'a month ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 4, 'description': "Amazing ambience with gorgeous high ceiling bar. [{'rating': 5, 'description': "What a hidden gem!!!
Went out for lunch with my colleagues and we were so happy as we stepped in until we departed. Very well decorated ambient as high class French restaurant with great customer service literally by every crew in the restaurant. Every menu came out highly presentable and the taste to remember. Choices of wine are so great as well.  Highly recommended. I'll definitely go back every time I visit Singapore.", 'date': '2 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'We came on Saturday and ordered the tasting menu. The food is great with excellent service! The degustation set lunch is $98 per person and it‚Äôs quite affordable especially the number of dishes and quality. Highly recommended place', 'date': '3 weeks ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': "Came here to celebrate birthday, the chef helped us to take a nice photo, I was wondering how come he never wished me happy birthday, and none of the waiters wished me happy birthday. After the meal when I went home I then realized my reservation was for the next day lol!!!!

But the waiters was so polite that when I told him I made a reservation for two pax, they obviously couldn't find it but they still got me a nice table without embarrasing me by telling me no reservation was made. ^^
PLEASE share the story with the chef, he obviously didn't know what happened cos I just stood up and wanted to leave cos I felt a bit neglected, when he asked me how was the food I said very good and left in a hurry. :p

Food was obviously excellent and service was impeccable, thanks so much for for everything, we will be back~", 'date': '3 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': "We came on a weekend night and had a great time there. Five stars food and five stars service. The interior is minimalistic where tables are arranged around an open concept kitchen counter, there is a private room that sits 8-10 pax at the back. Expect nothing less for food presentation, dishes were colorful like how French cuisine is supposed to be. Great attention to details e.g. micro slices on our king oyster mushroom pieces, symmetry of the ensembles, etc. Of all the dishes from our Degustation set, we enjoyed the starter, Le Crabe, the most as the dish was very light and refreshing. Lobster bisque was outstanding and scallop carpacio melted in our mouths. At the end of the main courses prior to desserts, cheeses were served. As it was my wife's birthday, we got a complementary cake as well. The sommelier was knowledgeable and our wine pairing was pleasant.  Chef Alexandre was very friendly and chatted with us throughout the course. For what it's worth, I think the charges were very fair. I definitely recommend this place for a good night out.", 'date': '5 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'Every single dishes touched my heart.
Chef Alex and his team are wow wow wow!!Amazing! Excellent! Fantastic! So satisfying lunch:) visiting there soonest. Highly recommended.', 'date': '5 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'I visited Fleur De Sel Le for my boyfriend‚Äôs birthday, and their service was amazing!
I didn‚Äôt even ask for birthday plate but they prepared a chocolate cake for him, which was sooo goodü§§
We‚Äôd like to come back someday for special occasions!!', 'date': '4 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': "When I reserved a table at Fleur De Sel, I was only thinking of just enjoying some nice French food at a modern setting, and oh boy, this restaurant brings so much more onto the table. I'm totally impressed since I enjoy the complete set of classic French hospitality here: complimentary Bread with French butter, the Canap√©s, the pouring of sauces over the dishes in front of the patrons (I miss this nice little gesture so much, my last experiences with this were at Odette and French restaurants of such caliber many years ago), the French palate cleanser and the Petit Fours.

Best of all, I get to enjoyed these without costing an arm or a leg. And yes, lots of videos ensured to capture the pouring of sauces. Feel free to request the friendly and patient staff to hold on for a while while getting the video mode ready. By the way, the service here is exceptional. It really takes me to the days of dining at classic French restaurants that achieve perfection in service.

The setting of the restaurant is contemporary and classy, with the colour white as main theme. I can really feel that I'm in a fancy French restaurant here (the French songs playing in the background helps with that), but without the dining-is-serious-business vibe due to the modern feel of the place. So I feel very ease here actually and loving it lol

The real show begins when Le Crabe is served. The rich-in-flavours ingredients really work their magic here. Briny fresh crab, buttery n grassy avocado and refreshingly, mildly sweet balsamic sorbet work so well together. I love this creamy treat.

The awesome dining journey continues with La Saint-Jacques. The seared succulent plump Hokkaido scallop has this amazing pan seared surface that is slightly crispy and carries an iota of smokiness, Butternut squash pur√©e adds the earthy sweetness while Parma ham introduces bits of excitement into the taste.

Lychee granita is one of the best palate cleansers I have. I love the sweet floral taste of lychee and the minuscule bites of lychee gives a nice variation in texture.

Le Baba is oh-so-good. In fact, I heard the patrons at a neighbouring table swooning over this.

The service staff will slice the baba cake in half in front of the patrons. And the cake actually jiggle a bit when the knife slice through it: a testimony to how fluffy it is. And a look at the interior proves it. Next comes the Bailey's. The staff will enquire on the preferred amount of Bailey's to be added prior to adding it in. Lastly, the generous amount of light and fresh creamy Vanilla cream is added onto the Baba. This hits the right spot in both taste and texture. The cream and the tart taste of passionfruit glaze juxtapose so well with the herbal bitterness of Bailey's.

This is a must-try here.

I'm really surprised by how intricate the dining experience here, and I feel so pampered when dining here. By the way, there is no dress code, so one can enjoy fine French food in a relaxing ambience and clothing. This is one of the places I will recommend to experience the full extent of French dining while not over-stressing the wallet.

Thoughts: Lovely French Restaurant for Indulgence", 'date': '6 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 4, 'description': 'Service - top notch. They serviced us very well. Felt like a million bucks. Awesome much!

Premise - very cute to be honest. The decor was nice. The place felt very pish posh. Very clean everything at the premise. Sanitary goodness.

Food - it was lunch menu, we had the set. We ordered both sets - 78+++ and 98+++. It was all fantastic. Nothing to say bad about because all were awesome. From the starters to the ending of the meal, we could not have had anything negative to say.

Verdict - can come again with clients and also to impress the date. Price also was not that mind-blowing TBH.', 'date': '9 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}]

review_sample:
[{'rating': 5, 'description': 'Wonderful view
So great for sunset

We only ate the truffle gnocchi & giant 1 pound meatball, be forewarned it is a meal all by itself.
The meat ball was great quality meat, my hubby said it was dry for his taste and the sauce saved it but I felt it was pretty juicy, so to each their own
The truffle gnocchi was absolute PERFECTION. The gnocchi was a good size and not to soft or mushy like it can get sometimes. The truffle flavor was very pronounced just the way I like itS and I particularly love that they shredded the truffle like a garnish on top rather than just one huge chunk of truffle. That way I could get a bite truffle and every single mouthful.

And at the end they surprised us with a happy anniversary cake and I have to say that cake was surprisingly good. I really enjoyed it.', 'date': 'a week ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'Went here for a night date and it was amazing. ‚Äúthe meatball‚Äù (6) - quite unimpressed given that this is LAVO's signature appetizer. It basically tastes like a giant meatball without any special appeal in terms of aesthetic or taste. Feels more like a comfort food for westerners

silk handkerchief (7) - although it tastes better than the meatball, it tastes like a blend of pasta and shepherd's pie. No strong standout attribute as well. Feels more like a comfort food for westerners

Making your drinks on the day to day would be his prot√©g√©, Shah. A handsome young man who‚Äôs more like a son than an employee. But rest assured, you‚Äôll be in great hands no matter what.

[{'rating': 5, 'description': 'Kuriya is a Japanese restaurant located in the Great World City shopping mall in Singapore. The restaurant has a modern and sleek design, with a spacious dining area and a sushi bar where diners can watch the chefs at work.

All of the dishes are expertly prepared and beautifully presented, with a focus on using the freshest ingredients available.

The sushi in particular is a highlight of the menu. The fish is incredibly fresh and melts in your mouth, and the rice is perfectly cooked and seasoned. The sashimi platters are also a great option for those who want to try a variety of raw fish.

Another great aspect of Kuriya is the attentive service. The staff are friendly and knowledgeable, and are always on hand to offer recommendations or answer any questions you may have. They also provide a warm and welcoming atmosphere, making you feel right at home.

The prices at Kuriya are on the higher side, but the quality of the food and service more than justifies the cost. Nevertheless, we got everything we needed, and staff did all the necessary for a fine dining restaurant such as pulling our seats back and forward as we sat down. So far, so good. We ordered 2 executive set lunches, and I opted to top up $18 for the Wagyu rump. We selected the carpaccio and truffle mushroom soup for starters. The carpaccio was very thinly sliced and not bad, but the mushroom soup lacked oomph, and I couldn't taste much truffle. I've had heartier mushroom soups at buffet lines, so not a good start food wise. For the mains, we had the farro risotto, and I got the Wagyu rump...which was quite a mistake because despite paying an extra $18, I got a slab of beef that was perhaps 150 to 180g tops, which I couldn't tell was Wagyu, as it lacked any discernible marbling, and was even a tad powdery. My wife enjoyed her risotto much more, but I wasn't a fan either. By then I was quite disappointed with the food, and the dessert didn't do much to redeem the meal. Chocolate popsicle and croissant cheesecake were passable, looked great but taste was average. 5 stars for ambience, 4 stars for service, 3 stars for taste of food. review_sample:
[{'rating': 5, 'description': 'Been wanting to try this as they are the 2nd best bar in Asia, making it 1st in Singapore.

address: 29 Tanglin Road, The St. Regis Singapore, Level 1U, Singapore 247912
review_sample:
[{'rating': 5, 'description': "Since opening in The St. Regis Singapore hotel in December 2007, Yan Ting restaurant has been a stalwart of the Chinese Cantonese fine dining scene, the epitome of extravagance and luxury. These days, there are plenty of Chinese fine dining restaurants around, but Yan Ting has certainly stepped up their game, remaining a premium dining destination of choice, serving well-executed and refined gastronomic delights on each plate.
.
Ambience at Yan Ting is opulent. The grandeur of the interior exudes a classy elegance, without being too over the top. The tastefully arranged layout is suitable for business or private dining, and the decor enhances the overall ambience without being too loud. I also like the bright ambient lighting, which isn't too harsh or dim. The pearl marble floors and plush furnishings feel sophisticated and comfortable.
.
Service at Yan Ting restaurant is professional, discreet, and polite. Staff may not make much conversation, but they are attentive and observant. The accord each table good attention, answering queries, fulfilling requests, serving orders, and proactively clearing finished plates with finesse. Communication in English or Chinese Mandarin is decent. Felt very well treated here.
.
Food at Yan Ting follows the Chinese Cantonese philosophy of freshness of ingredients, little usage of herbs, and well balanced dishes that are naturally flavourful but not greasy. Yan Ting restaurant prepares classic Chinese Cantonese dishes according to time-honoured recipes, but presents them in beautiful contemporary style.
.
Portions are sized for individuals, but dishes are best shared. Prices are high. Prepare to splurge, budget about SGD $245 per person for a meal here.", 'date': 'a month ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'We were here on our vegetarian routine day. However you might need to wait for up to 30-45 mins to serve your food.', 'date': '3 weeks ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 4, 'description': 'We were hosted to lunch here, and the place was packed at 12 noon, so much so that reservations are a must.  One negative is that the place was too loud, with so many people talking, that I ended up with a headache.  Having a normal-level conversation was quite difficult.

Service was quite warm and quick, and the waitstaff were always quick to top up our teas.

The food was generally of a high standard, though some meat dishes were rather tough.  The pork jowl done charsiu style was tasty, but some pieces were tough to bite through or chew.  Similarly, not all pieces of the stir fried beef, which was delish, were soft.

The xiqolong bao was nce, but the standout dish for me was the siew mai. We ordered desserts of sago with mango , and quilingao, both of which made for a sweet ending to the meal.', 'date': '3 weeks ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'Had dim sum, shunde fish tofu and cabbage, and their specialty kung-fu soup for lunch today, and the dishes were well executed and presented hot and fresh. A very pleasant lunch at Yan Ting!', 'date': '3 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'We recently had the pleasure of dining at Yan Ting. The staffs (Bruce and Yong Zhe) were incredibly friendly and accommodating.

The food was absolutely delicious and the presentation was beautiful. The atmosphere was warm and inviting. The service was top notch and the staffs were very knowledgeable about the menu.

I would highly recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for a fine dining experience. The staffs were attentive and made sure that our experience was enjoyable. I would definitely come back again!', 'date': '6 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 2, 'description': "Visited the place on 23/7/23 - Are we unlucky on the day or the demographics who go there don‚Äôt do google reviews at all ?

This is not a criticism of any specific members of staff but rather the management of the establishment,  which is shocking for such a reputedly upscale restaurant. The entire work flow from the reception down to the kitchen need to be reviewed by the management.

When I walked into the restaurant at 12:40pm, there was already a commotion of staff running around, no one even stopped or batted an eye to notice anyone going in or going out. There was no one at the reception to welcome guests either.  After we placed our order, it took them 20 mins to serve a single basket of Har gow and this was only after we nudged the staff. Our jaw dropped when after 20 minutes, only one basket of dim sum was served.  It took an additional 10 minutes to deliver a separate second plate of radish cake. The remaining dishes were served after another 20 minutes. Overall, it took them between 50 mins to an hour to serve up all dishes and there were only two of us with a moderate order list.

We later tried to order the pan-fried glutinous rice hoping the kitchen chaos would have died down but were informed that there will be a one-hour wait to prepare the dish ! O....k.......... We didn't proceed of course.

They appear to be VERY understaffed, in which case they should not have accepted so many reservations in the first place. Staff were running around like headless chickens freaking out, there were also voices raised talking to each other. It was a very distressing scene while trying to have a peaceful meal.

We also saw some elderly customers going up to the staff to complain. There was zero recovery service.

I hate to say this but I‚Äôve had better hospitality and services at any regular Chinese restaurant in a shopping mall.  As for the presentation of the food, you can judge for yourself.  Unfortunately, even Kimly dim sum have had better presentation in a styrofoam box.  I‚Äôm a CCF lover and the steam rice roll was the saddest I‚Äôve ever seen.

The ingredients are fresh but that‚Äôs the baseline of any decent dim sum restaurant anyway.  2 stars for the staff doing their best despite what I believed is terrible management.

Fortunately it was a casual meetup with a friend. It would have been embarrassing if we were entertaining business associates.

:(", 'date': '2 months ago', 'images': ['https://storage.googleapis.com/synthesis_geos_public/thumbnails/thumb_unavail.jpg']}, {'rating': 5, 'description': 'One of the best chinese fine dining restaurants in Singapore. Can always trust Yan Ting to provide the best experience.
